<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9793> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9793" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Additions and Corrections. The name of Ser. Sulpicius Galba appears alone in the date on a recently published inscription of the Campanian magistri (De Franciscis, Epigraphica 12 [1950] 126-130, pub. Dec. 1951), and probably gives an indication of the period after the condemnation of Hortensius and before the election of Aurelius Scaurus as Consul Suffectus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8667> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8667" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 743" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3549> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3549" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Captured and killed by the Cimbri while serving under the Consul Mallius (Liv. Per. 67; Gran. Lic. 17 B; Oros. 5.16.2, Aemilius; cf. Vell. 2.12.2; Tac. Germ. 37; Dio 27, fr. 91; Ps.-Quintil. Decl. 3.13)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3524> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3524" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably served under Servilius Caepio in Gaul this year (see 105, Legates).{555}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3480> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3480" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 1\n     .2.675, 676; Fast. Ant., Degrassi 162f. (M. Aureli. Scaur.); Fast. Cap., Degrassi 54f. ([- - - -] Scaurus); Obseq. 40 (M. Scauro); Fast. Hyd. (Scauro), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod. See Degrassi 127, 476f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3479> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3479" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The conclusion already reached in 1909 by Bloch that the Scaurus who was Cos. Suff. in 108 was not named M. Aemilius but M. Aurelius has since been confirmed by the Fasti of Antium (Bibl. Fac. Lett. Univ. Paris, 25.79ff.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3431> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3431" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible date under the Lex Villia." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3363> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3363" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Div. in Caec. 63; Ps.-Ascon. 203 Stangl; cf. Cic. Verr. 2.1.85. The date is a conjecture based on the interval frequent in this period between the quaestorship and the consulship. See below, Promagistrates, on Flaccus. See Sobeck 22." .
